   - `Directory.GetFiles` - static method (I/O side effect)\n   - `File.ReadAllText` - static method (I/O side effect)\n\nThe key insight is that I only need to wrap the problematic ones—those with side effects or non-deterministic behavior. Pure utility methods like `Path.Combine` or `string.Join` don't require wrapping since they're deterministic and have no side effects.","outputTokens":619,"requestId":"BD11:21BACA:1CB49D5:20794DB:6A07C70E"},"id":"31062936-7334-43f6-b1a8-4570d6810640","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:23:38.016Z","parentId":"db88be7c-b3bf-463e-8602-c532ebefcc31"}
